{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876578920,"sessionID":"ses_2858327ebffeT1wJYh76T71bKz","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7d2c9e001iu4MHy6G949Cg5","messageID":"msg_d7a7cffe7001fpPSUl3KWQvYoB","sessionID":"ses_2858327ebffeT1wJYh76T71bKz","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-e6bb4f8932274a0c9191b3ebde6ea503","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-027 Implementation Notes\n\n## Implementation Status\n- [ ] Design document\n- [ ] API specification\n- [ ] Client implementation\n- [ ] Error handling\n- [ ] Tests\n- [ ] Documentation\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Files Created\n\n[To be filled during implementation]\n\n### Test Coverage\n\n[To be filled during implementation]\n\n### API Contract\n\n[To be filled during implementation]\n\n### Notes\n\n[To be filled during implementation]","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/README.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/README.md","time":{"start":1775876578891,"end":1775876578919}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876578922,"sessionID":"ses_2858327ebffeT1wJYh76T71bKz","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7d5e84001cKilY7tYjX8A7w","messageID":"msg_d7a7cffe7001fpPSUl3KWQvYoB","sessionID":"ses_2858327ebffeT1wJYh76T71bKz","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-c35545c95ddc4a6b88b1675bc120f79b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-027 — SDK CodeInterpreterClient Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThe CodeInterpreterClient is a Python SDK that provides a high-level interface for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service. It abstracts the underlying HTTP communication and provides a clean, type-safe API for managing code execution sessions.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n1. **CodeInterpreterClient**: Main client class for interacting with the CodeInterpreter service\n2. **Session Manager**: Manages CodeInterpreter session lifecycle\n3. **Execution Manager**: Handles code execution requests\n4. **Result Processor**: Processes and validates execution results\n\n### Key Features\n\n- Session creation, retrieval, and termination\n- Code execution with synchronous and asynchronous modes\n- Result streaming and batch retrieval\n- Error handling and retry logic\n- Type-safe request/response models\n\n## API Design\n\n### Client Initialization\n\n```python\nfrom agentcube.sdk import CodeInterpreterClient\n\nclient = CodeInterpreterClient(\n    base_url=\"http://localhost:8080\",\n    api_key=\"your-api-key\"\n)\n```\n\n### Session Management\n\n```python\n# Create session\nsession = client.create_session(\n    workspace_id=\"workspace-123\",\n    timeout=300\n)\n\n# Get session\nsession = client.get_session(session_id=\"session-123\")\n\n# List sessions\nsessions = client.list_sessions(workspace_id=\"workspace-123\")\n\n# Delete session\nclient.delete_session(session_id=\"session-123\")\n```\n\n### Code Execution\n\n```python\n# Execute code synchronously\nresult = client.execute_code(\n    session_id=\"session-123\",\n    code=\"print('Hello, World!')\"\n)\n\n# Execute code asynchronously\njob = client.execute_code_async(\n    session_id=\"session-123\",\n    code=\"x = 1 + 1\"\n)\n\n# Get execution result\nresult = client.get_execution_result(job_id=\"job-123\")\n```\n\n## Data Models\n\n### Session\n\n```python\nclass Session(BaseModel):\n    session_id: str\n    workspace_id: str\n    status: SessionStatus\n    created_at: datetime\n    updated_at: datetime\n    timeout: int\n```\n\n### ExecutionResult\n\n```python\nclass ExecutionResult(BaseModel):\n    job_id: str\n    session_id: str\n    status: ExecutionStatus\n    output: str\n    error: Optional[str]\n    execution_time: float\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n- Custom exception types for different error scenarios\n- Automatic retry logic for transient errors\n- Detailed error messages with context\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- Unit tests for client methods\n- Integration tests with mock CodeInterpreter service\n- End-to-end tests with real service (when available)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- httpx ^0.24.0 (HTTP client)\n- pydantic ^2.0.0 (data validation)\n- typing-extensions ^4.0.0 (type hints)\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n- WebSocket support for streaming output\n- Session persistence and recovery\n- Advanced debugging features\n- Custom execution environment configuration","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-027/design.md","time":{"start":1775876578894,"end":1775876578921}}}}
